{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849579938,"sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","part":{"id":"prt_d78e2173d001pB4p0ee16rTGCf","messageID":"msg_d78e2081b0014ugAddaXAWA50m","sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7196d3bd755d44d5ada5f4e4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-011\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/router`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirement: JWT Configuration\n23: \n24: ### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with default configuration\n25: \n26: **GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `jwtEnabled: true` and no explicit JWT configuration\n27: **WHEN** the router initializes\n28: **THEN** it SHOULD use default values: secret from environment or config, algorithm \"HS256\", expiry \"1h\"\n29: \n30: ### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with custom configuration\n31: \n32: **GIVEN** a Router instance with JWT configuration: `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"`, `jwtExpiry: \"24h\"`, `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n33: **WHEN** the router initializes\n34: **THEN** it SHOULD configure RS256 algorithm, 24 hour expiry, and issuer to \"agentcube\"\n35: \n36: ### Scenario: Router disables JWT authentication\n37: \n38: **GIVEN** a Router instance with `jwtEnabled: false` (default)\n39: **WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n40: **THEN** the router SHOULD NOT validate JWT tokens\n41: **AND** no JWT middleware SHOULD be applied\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n46: \n47: ### Scenario: Router validates valid JWT token\n48: \n49: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and configured secret\n50: **WHEN** a request arrives with a valid JWT token in Authorization header \"Bearer <valid-token>\"\n51: **THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n52: **AND** extract the claims into the request context\n53: \n54: ### Scenario: Router rejects expired JWT token\n55: \n56: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n57: **WHEN** a request arrives with an expired JWT token\n58: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n59: **AND** return 401 Unauthorized with appropriate error message\n60: \n61: ### Scenario: Router rejects invalid signature JWT token\n62: \n63: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n64: **WHEN** a request arrives with a JWT token that has invalid signature\n65: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n66: **AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid signature\" error\n67: \n68: ### Scenario: Router rejects malformed JWT token\n69: \n70: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n71: **WHEN** a request arrives with a malformed JWT token (not 3 parts)\n72: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n73: **AND** return 400 Bad Request with \"malformed token\" error\n74: \n75: ### Scenario: Router extracts claims from valid JWT\n76: \n77: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n78: **WHEN** a request arrives with valid JWT containing claims: `sub`, `exp`, `roles`\n79: **THEN** the claims SHOULD be available in request context\n80: **AND** can be accessed by downstream handlers\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Requirement: JWT Token Issuance\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT token for valid credentials\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint configured\n89: **WHEN** a POST request arrives with valid username and password\n90: **THEN** the router SHOULD authenticate the credentials\n91: **AND** issue a JWT token with user claims\n92: **AND** return the token in the response\n93: \n94: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured expiry\n95: \n96: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtExpiry: \"2h\"`\n97: **WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n98: **THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `exp` claim set to current time + 2 hours\n99: \n100: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured issuer\n101: \n102: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n103: **WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n104: **THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `iss` claim set to \"agentcube\"\n105: \n106: ### Scenario: Router rejects invalid credentials\n107: \n108: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint\n109: **WHEN** a POST request arrives with invalid username or password\n110: **THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n111: **AND** NOT issue a JWT token\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## Requirement: JWT Middleware\n116: \n117: ### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from Authorization header\n118: \n119: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n120: **WHEN** a request arrives with header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n121: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token\n122: **AND** validate it\n123: \n124: ### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from query parameter\n125: \n126: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware configured to allow query param\n127: **WHEN** a request arrives with query param `?token=<token>`\n128: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token from query\n129: **AND** validate it\n130: \n131: ### Scenario: JWT middleware allows public endpoints\n132: \n133: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n134: **WHEN** a request arrives at a public endpoint (e.g., `/health`, `/login`)\n135: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD skip JWT validation\n136: **AND** allow the request through\n137: \n138: ### Scenario: JWT middleware blocks unauthorized access\n139: \n140: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n141: **WHEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint without token\n142: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Requirement: JWT Claims\n147: \n148: ### Scenario: Router includes user ID in JWT claims\n149: \n150: **GIVEN** a user logs in successfully\n151: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n152: **THEN** the token SHOULD include `sub` claim with user identifier\n153: \n154: ### Scenario: Router includes roles in JWT claims\n155: \n156: **GIVEN** a user with roles \"admin\", \"user\" logs in\n157: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n158: **THEN** the token SHOULD include `roles` claim with array [\"admin\", \"user\"]\n159: \n160: ### Scenario: Router includes custom claims in JWT\n161: \n162: **GIVEN** a Router configured with custom claims (e.g., `tenant_id`)\n163: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n164: **THEN** the token SHOULD include the custom claims\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Requirement: Token Refresh\n169: \n170: ### Scenario: Router supports token refresh endpoint\n171: \n172: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and refresh endpoint configured\n173: **WHEN** a valid (non-expired) JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n174: **THEN** a new JWT token SHOULD be issued\n175: **AND** the new token SHOULD have fresh expiry time\n176: \n177: ### Scenario: Router rejects refresh with expired token\n178: \n179: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT refresh enabled\n180: **WHEN** an expired JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n181: **THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Requirement: Key Management\n186: \n187: ### Scenario: Router loads JWT secret from configuration\n188: \n189: **GIVEN** a Router with `jwtSecret: \"my-secret-key\"` configured\n190: **WHEN** JWT validation or issuance occurs\n191: **THEN** the router SHOULD use \"my-secret-key\" for signing/verification\n192: \n193: ### Scenario: Router supports RS256 with private key\n194: \n195: **GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and private key configured\n196: **WHEN** JWT token is issued\n197: **THEN** the token SHOULD be signed with RS256 using the private key\n198: \n199: ### Scenario: Router validates RS256 token with public key\n200: \n201: **GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and public key configured\n202: **WHEN** a request arrives with RS256-signed JWT\n203: **THEN** the router SHOULD validate using the public key\n204: \n205: ### Scenario: Router validates audience claim\n206: \n207: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n208: **WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"agentcube-api\"`\n209: **THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n210: \n211: ### Scenario: Router rejects token with wrong audience\n212: \n213: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n214: **WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"other-api\"`\n215: **THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n216: **AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid audience\" error\n217: \n218: ### Scenario: Router handles clock skew\n219: \n220: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and clock skew tolerance configured\n221: **WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that expires within the clock skew window\n222: **THEN** the router SHOULD accept the token as valid\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## Requirement: JWT Metrics\n227: \n228: ### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation success\n229: \n230: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n231: **WHEN** a valid JWT is successfully validated\n232: **THEN** the metric `jwt_validated_total` SHOULD be incremented with label `result=\"success\"`\n233: \n234: ### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation failure\n235: \n236: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n237: **WHEN** a JWT validation fails (expired, invalid signature, etc.)\n238: **THEN** the metric `jwt_validation_errors_total` SHOULD be incremented\n239: **AND** include error type label\n240: \n241: ### Scenario: Router tracks JWT token issuance\n242: \n243: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n244: **WHEN** a JWT token is successfully issued\n245: **THEN** the metric `jwt_issued_total` SHOULD be incremented\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Acceptance Criteria\n250: \n251: - [ ] JWT tokens are validated on protected endpoints\n252: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected with 401\n253: - [ ] Invalid signatures are rejected with 401\n254: - [ ] Valid tokens expose claims in request context\n255: - [ ] Login endpoint issues JWT tokens\n256: - [ ] Token expiry is configurable\n257: - [ ] Token issuer is configurable\n258: - [ ] JWT algorithm is configurable (HS256, RS256)\n259: - [ ] Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n260: - [ ] Token refresh endpoint works correctly\n261: - [ ] Custom claims can be included in tokens\n262: - [ ] Invalid credentials are rejected\n263: - [ ] Audience claim is validated when configured\n264: - [ ] Clock skew is handled gracefully\n265: - [ ] JWT metrics are exported (jwt_validated_total, jwt_issued_total, jwt_validation_errors_total)\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ## References\n270: \n271: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n272: - Proposal: `proposal.md`\n\n(End of file - total 272 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-011\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775849579913,"end":1775849579936}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849579940,"sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","part":{"id":"prt_d78e21c5d001FeMmRmYDT54fsX","messageID":"msg_d78e2081b0014ugAddaXAWA50m","sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2698c0315a1d4edaa7acc3ef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/router  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Session Configuration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Add session config fields to `Config` struct — `SessionEnabled`, `SessionTimeout`, `SessionCookieName`, `SessionMaxActive`, `SessionCookieSecure`, `SessionCookieHTTPOnly`, `SessionCookieDomain`\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` session defaults — timeout `30m`, cookie `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max `10000`, cleanup `5m`\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Add session cleanup interval config — `SessionCleanupInterval` with default `5m`\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Phase 2: Session Data Structures\n19: \n20: - [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/session.go` — `Session` struct with ID, Backend, CreatedAt, LastActivity, ExpiresAt, Metadata fields\n21: - [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/router/session.go` — `SessionStore` interface (Create, Get, Update, Delete, List, Cleanup)\n22: - [ ] **2.3** Implement in-memory `MemorySessionStore` — thread-safe map with RWMutex\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Phase 3: Session ID Generation\n27: \n28: - [ ] **3.1** Implement `GenerateSessionID()` — return UUID v4 using `github.com/google/uuid`\n29: - [ ] **3.2** Write unit test: Generate 1000 IDs, verify all unique\n30: - [ ] **3.3** Write unit test: Verify UUID v4 format\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Phase 4: Session Storage Operations\n35: \n36: - [ ] **4.1** Implement `SessionStore.Create()` — create session with generated ID, backend ref, timestamps\n37: - [ ] **4.2** Implement `SessionStore.Get()` — retrieve by session ID, return nil if not found\n38: - [ ] **4.3** Implement `SessionStore.Update()` — update last activity time\n39: - [ ] **4.4** Implement `SessionStore.Delete()` — remove session by ID\n40: - [ ] **4.5** Implement `SessionStore.List()` — return all active sessions\n41: - [ ] **4.6** Implement max session limit enforcement — reject new session when at limit\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Phase 5: Session Middleware\n46: \n47: - [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/router/session_middleware.go` — extract session from cookie `AGENTSESSIONID`\n48: - [ ] **5.2** Create `pkg/router/session_middleware.go` — extract session from header `X-Session-ID`\n49: - [ ] **5.3** Create new session if none found — generate ID, set response cookie\n50: - [ ] **5.4** Update last activity on each request — extend expiration on activity\n51: - [ ] **5.5** Integrate middleware into router handler chain\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Phase 6: Session Expiration\n56: \n57: - [ ] **6.1** Implement session expiration check — mark expired based on `ExpiresAt`\n58: - [ ] **6.2** Implement sliding expiration — reset `ExpiresAt` on activity\n59: - [ ] **6.3** Reject requests with expired session — return new session\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## Phase 7: Session Cleanup\n64: \n65: - [ ] **7.1** Implement periodic cleanup goroutine — run every cleanup interval\n66: - [ ] **7.2** Implement `Cleanup()` method — remove all expired sessions\n67: - [ ] **7.3** Add cleanup to router lifecycle — start on Start(), stop on Shutdown()\n68: - [ ] **7.4** Write unit test: Verify expired sessions are removed\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Phase 8: Session Affinity (Sticky Sessions)\n73: \n74: - [ ] **8.1** Store backend reference in session — on new session creation\n75: - [ ] **8.2** Route request to session's assigned backend — use stored backend key\n76: - [ ] **8.3** Handle backend removal — invalidate session when backend removed\n77: - [ ] **8.4** Write unit test: Verify same session routes to same backend\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Phase 9: Session Cookie Configuration\n82: \n83: - [ ] **9.1** Set cookie `Secure` flag — when `SessionCookieSecure: true`\n84: - [ ] **9.2** Set cookie `HttpOnly` flag — when `SessionCookieHTTPOnly: true`\n85: - [ ] **9.3** Set cookie `Domain` — when `SessionCookieDomain` configured\n86: - [ ] **9.4** Set cookie `Path` — default to `/`\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Phase 10: Session Metrics\n91: \n92: - [ ] **10.1** Add `router_sessions_active` gauge — track active session count\n93: - [ ] **10.2** Add `router_sessions_created_total` counter — track session creation\n94: - [ ] **10.3** Add `router_sessions_expired_total` counter — track expiration\n95: - [ ] **10.4** Add `router_session_duration_seconds` histogram — track session lifetime\n96: - [ ] **10.5** Update metrics on create/expire/cleanup events\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Phase 11: Graceful Shutdown\n101: \n102: - [ ] **11.1** Stop accepting new sessions on shutdown\n103: - [ ] **11.2** Wait for cleanup goroutine to finish\n104: - [ ] **11.3** Ensure existing sessions remain available during shutdown\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## Phase 12: Verification\n109: \n110: - [ ] **12.1** `go build ./pkg/router/...` — successful compilation\n111: - [ ] **12.2** `go test ./pkg/router/... -v` — all unit tests pass\n112: - [ ] **12.3** Test: Default session config creates store with correct defaults\n113: - [ ] **12.4** Test: Custom session config overrides defaults\n114: - [ ] **12.5** Test: Session middleware extracts from cookie\n115: - [ ] **12.6** Test: Session middleware extracts from header\n116: - [ ] **12.7** Test: New session sets response cookie\n117: - [ ] **12.8** Test: Sticky session routes to same backend\n118: - [ ] **12.9** Test: Session expires after timeout\n119: - [ ] **12.10** Test: Cleanup removes expired sessions\n120: - [ ] **12.11** Test: Metrics reflect session state changes\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## Dependencies\n125: \n126: - `github.com/google/uuid` — Session ID generation\n127: - `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` — Metrics\n128: - AR-009 (completed) — Router core infrastructure\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## References\n133: \n134: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`\n135: - Design: `pkg/router/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 135 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Session Configuration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Add session config fields to `Config` struct — `SessionEnabled`, `SessionTimeout`, `SessionCookieName`, `SessionMaxActive`, `SessionCookieSecure`, `SessionCookieHTTPOnly`, `SessionCookieDomain`\n- [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` session defaults — timeout `30m`, cookie `\"AGENTSESSIONID\"`, max `10000`, cleanup `5m`\n- [ ] **1.3** Add session cleanup interval config — `SessionCleanupInterval` with default `5m`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Session Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/session.go` — `Session` struct with ID, Backend, CreatedAt, LastActivity, ExpiresAt, Metadata fields","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775849579916,"end":1775849579938}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849579943,"sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","part":{"id":"prt_d78e22144001nhtQb8Mf8Jy333","messageID":"msg_d78e2081b0014ugAddaXAWA50m","sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7aa7d9edd7304584a703cf2d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-011\n4: - **Module**: `pkg/router`\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: Draft\n8: - **Base**: AR-010 (Session Management)\n9: \n10: ## 1. 概述\n11: \n12: 本设计文档聚焦于 **JWT 认证与签发** 功能，为 `pkg/router` 模块增加基于 JWT 的身份验证和令牌管理能力。该功能是 AR-010 会话管理的扩展，提供安全的 API 访问控制。\n13: \n14: ### 1.1 目标\n15: \n16: - 实现 JWT Token 验证（支持 HS256、RS256 算法）\n17: - 实现 JWT Token 签发（登录接口）\n18: - 实现 Token 刷新接口\n19: - 支持可配置的 JWT 参数（Issuer、Audience、Expiry）\n20: - 提供 JWT 指标监控\n21: \n22: ### 1.2 依赖\n23: \n24: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` — JWT 令牌处理\n25: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` — 现有路由模块\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. 架构设计\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 整体架构\n32: \n33: ```\n34: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n35: │                         Router Server (pkg/router)                       │\n36: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐    │\n37: │  │   JWT       │→ │  Auth       │→ │  Rate Limit │→ │   Proxy     │    │\n38: │  │ Middleware  │  │ Middleware  │  │  Middleware  │  │   Handler   │    │\n39: │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘    │\n40: │         │                                                                    │\n41: │  ┌──────▼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐         │\n42: │  │                    JWT Manager                               │         │\n43: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐         │         │\n44: │  │  │   Token     │  │   Token     │  │   Key       │         │         │\n45: │  │  │  Validation│  │  Issuance   │  │  Management │         │         │\n46: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘         │         │\n47: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘         │\n48: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### 2.2 组件职责\n52: \n53: | 组件 | 职责 |\n54: |------|------|\n55: | `JWTMiddleware` | 拦截请求，提取并验证 JWT Token |\n56: | `JWTManager` | 核心 JWT 操作：签发、验证、刷新 |\n57: | `KeyManager` | 密钥管理（HS256 对称密钥、RS256 非对称密钥） |\n58: | `LoginHandler` | 处理用户登录，签发 Token |\n59: | `RefreshHandler` | 处理 Token 刷新 |\n60: \n61: ### 2.3 数据流\n62: \n63: ```\n64: 1. 客户端请求进入 Router\n65:    │\n66: 2. JWTMiddleware 检查公开端点\n67:    ├── 公开端点 → 跳过验证，继续处理\n68:    │\n69: 3. JWTMiddleware 提取 Token\n70:    ├── 从 Header: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n71:    ├── 或从 Query: ?token=<token>\n72:    │\n73: 4. JWTManager 验证 Token\n74:    ├── 检查签名\n75:    ├── 检查过期时间\n76:    ├── 检查 Issuer\n77:    ├── 检查 Audience\n78:    │\n79: 5. 验证通过 → 将 Claims 写入 Context → 传递给下游 Handler\n80:    │\n81: 6. 验证失败 → 返回 401 Unauthorized\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## 3. 数据结构\n87: \n88: ### 3.1 JWT 配置\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: // JWTConfig holds JWT-specific configuration\n92: type JWTConfig struct {\n93:     Enabled         bool          // Enable JWT authentication (default: false)\n94:     Algorithm       string        // Algorithm: \"HS256\" or \"RS256\" (default: \"HS256\")\n95:     Secret          string        // Secret key for HS256\n96:     PrivateKeyPath  string        // Path to RSA private key for RS256\n97:     PublicKeyPath   string        // Path to RSA public key for RS256\n98:     Issuer          string        // Token issuer (default: \"agentcube\")\n99:     Audience        []string      // Expected audience claims\n100:     Expiration      time.Duration // Token expiration (default: 1h)\n101:     RefreshExpiration time.Duration // Refresh token expiration (default: 24h)\n102:     ClockSkew       time.Duration // Clock skew tolerance (default: 30s)\n103:     AllowQueryParam bool          // Allow token in query parameter (default: false)\n104: }\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ### 3.2 JWT 声明\n108: \n109: ```go\n110: // Claims represents standard JWT claims\n111: type Claims struct {\n112:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n113:     // Custom claims\n114:     Roles     []string          `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n115:     TenantID  string            `json:\"tenant_id,omitempty\"`\n116:     Namespace string            `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n117: }\n118: \n119: // UserCredentials represents login request\n120: type UserCredentials struct {\n121:     Username string `json:\"username\" binding:\"required\"`\n122:     Password string `json:\"password\" binding:\"required\"`\n123: }\n124: \n125: // LoginResponse represents login response\n126: type LoginResponse struct {\n127:     AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`\n128:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`\n129:     TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`\n130:     ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`\n131: }\n132: \n133: // TokenRefreshRequest represents refresh token request\n134: type TokenRefreshRequest struct {\n135:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\" binding:\"required\"`\n136: }\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3.3 JWT 管理器\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: // JWTManager handles JWT token operations\n143: type JWTManager struct {\n144:     config          *JWTConfig\n145:     secretKey       []byte\n146:     privateKey      *rsa.PrivateKey\n147:     publicKey       *rsa.PublicKey\n148:     metrics         *JWTMetrics\n149:     userValidator   UserValidator\n150:     mu              sync.RWMutex\n151: }\n152: \n153: // UserValidator validates user credentials\n154: type UserValidator interface {\n155:     Validate(username, password string) (*UserClaims, error)\n156: }\n157: \n158: // UserClaims represents authenticated user info\n159: type UserClaims struct {\n160:     Username  string\n161:     Roles     []string\n162:     TenantID  string\n163:     Namespace string\n164: }\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ### 3.4 更新配置结构\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: // Config (extended from AR-010)\n171: type Config struct {\n172:     // ... existing fields ...\n173:     \n174:     // JWT settings\n175:     JWT JWTConfig // JWT configuration\n176: }\n177: \n178: // DefaultConfig returns config with JWT defaults\n179: func DefaultConfig() *Config {\n180:     return &Config{\n181:         // ... existing defaults ...\n182:         JWT: JWTConfig{\n183:             Enabled:         false,\n184:             Algorithm:       \"HS256\",\n185:             Secret:          \"\",\n186:             Issuer:          \"agentcube\",\n187:             Audience:        nil,\n188:             Expiration:      1 * time.Hour,\n189:             RefreshExpiration: 24 * time.Hour,\n190:             ClockSkew:       30 * time.Second,\n191:             AllowQueryParam: false,\n192:         },\n193:     }\n194: }\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ## 4. API 合约\n200: \n201: ### 4.1 新增端点\n202: \n203: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler | Description |\n204: |--------|------|------------|---------|-------------|\n205: | POST | `/login` | none | `handleLogin` | 用户登录，签发 Token |\n206: | POST | `/refresh` | none | `handleRefresh` | 刷新 Token |\n207: | GET | `/validate` | JWT | `handleValidate` | 验证当前 Token |\n208: \n209: ### 4.2 受保护端点（需 JWT）\n210: \n211: | Method | Path | Description |\n212: |--------|------|-------------|\n213: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/*path` | AgentRuntime 代理 |\n214: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/*path` | AgentRuntime 代理 |\n215: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/*path` | CodeInterpreter 代理 |\n216: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/*path` | CodeInterpreter 代理 |\n217: \n218: ### 4.3 公开端点（跳过 JWT）\n219: \n220: - `/health/live`\n221: - `/health/ready`\n222: - `/metrics`\n223: - `/login`\n224: - `/refresh`\n225: \n226: ### 4.4 登录请求/响应\n227: \n228: ```json\n229: // POST /login - Request\n230: {\n231:     \"username\": \"admin\",\n232:     \"password\": \"secret\"\n233: }\n234: \n235: // Response - Success\n236: {\n237:     \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n238:     \"refresh_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n239:     \"token_type\": \"Bearer\",\n240:     \"expires_in\": 3600\n241: }\n242: \n243: // Response - Error\n244: {\n245:     \"error\": \"invalid credentials\",\n246:     \"code\": \"ERR_INVALID_CREDENTIALS\",\n247:     \"requestId\": \"req-xxx\"\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### 4.5 Token 刷新请求/响应\n252: \n253: ```json\n254: // POST /refresh - Request\n255: {\n256:     \"refresh_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\"\n257: }\n258: \n259: // Response - Success\n260: {\n261:     \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n262:     \"token_type\": \"Bearer\",\n263:     \"expires_in\": 3600\n264: }\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ### 4.6 错误响应\n268: \n269: | Status Code | Description | Error Code |\n270: |-------------|-------------|------------|\n271: | 200 | Success | - |\n272: | 400 | Bad Request (malformed token) | `ERR_MALFORMED_TOKEN` |\n273: | 401 | Unauthorized (invalid/expired token) | `ERR_UNAUTHORIZED` |\n274: | 401 | Invalid credentials | `ERR_INVALID_CREDENTIALS` |\n275: | 401 | Invalid audience | `ERR_INVALID_AUDIENCE` |\n276: | 401 | Invalid issuer | `ERR_INVALID_ISSUER` |\n277: | 401 | Invalid signature | `ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE` |\n278: | 401 | Token expired | `ERR_TOKEN_EXPIRED` |\n279: | 401 | Invalid refresh token | `ERR_INVALID_REFRESH_TOKEN` |\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ## 5. 实现细节\n284: \n285: ### 5.1 JWT 验证流程\n286: \n287: ```go\n288: func (m *JWTManager) ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*Claims, error) {\n289:     // Parse token without validation first\n290:     token, _, err := jwt.NewParser().ParseUnverified(tokenString, &Claims{})\n291:     if err != nil {\n292:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrMalformedToken, err)\n293:     }\n294:     \n295:     // Select validation key based on algorithm\n296:     var validationKey interface{}\n297:     switch m.config.Algorithm {\n298:     case \"HS256\":\n299:         validationKey = m.secretKey\n300:     case \"RS256\":\n301:         validationKey = m.publicKey\n302:     }\n303:     \n304:     // Validate token\n305:     claims := &Claims{}\n306:     token, err = jwt.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, claims, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n307:         // Verify signing method\n308:         switch m.config.Algorithm {\n309:         case \"HS256\":\n310:             _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodHMAC)\n311:             if !ok {\n312:                 return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: unexpected signing method: %v\", ErrInvalidSignature, token.Header[\"alg\"])\n313:             }\n314:         case \"RS256\":\n315:             _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA)\n316:             if !ok {\n317:                 return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: unexpected signing method: %v\", ErrInvalidSignature, token.Header[\"alg\"])\n318:             }\n319:         }\n320:         return validationKey, nil\n321:     }, jwt.WithIssuer(m.config.Issuer),\n322:        jwt.WithAudience(m.config.Audience...),\n323:        jwt.WithClockSkew(m.config.ClockSkew))\n324:     \n325:     if err != nil {\n326:         if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenExpired) {\n327:             return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n328:         }\n329:         if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid) {\n330:             return nil, ErrInvalidSignature\n331:         }\n332:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrUnauthorized, err)\n333:     }\n334:     \n335:     return claims, nil\n336: }\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ### 5.2 JWT 签发流程\n340: \n341: ```go\n342: func (m *JWTManager) IssueToken(user *UserClaims) (string, error) {\n343:     now := time.Now()\n344:     \n345:     claims := Claims{\n346:         RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n347:             ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(now.Add(m.config.Expiration)),\n348:             IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(now),\n349:             NotBefore: jwt.NewNumericDate(now),\n350:             Issuer:    m.config.Issuer,\n351:             ID:        uuid.New().String(),\n352:         },\n353:         Roles:     user.Roles,\n354:         TenantID:  user.TenantID,\n355:         Namespace: user.Namespace,\n356:     }\n357:     \n358:     // Add audience if configured\n359:     if len(m.config.Audience) > 0 {\n360:         claims.Audience = m.config.Audience\n361:     }\n362:     \n363:     // Sign token based on algorithm\n364:     var tokenString string\n365:     var err error\n366:     \n367:     switch m.config.Algorithm {\n368:     case \"HS256\":\n369:         tokenString, err = jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodHS256, claims).SignedString(m.secretKey)\n370:     case \"RS256\":\n371:         tokenString, err = jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, claims).SignedString(m.privateKey)\n372:     default:\n373:         return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported algorithm: %s\", m.config.Algorithm)\n374:     }\n375:     \n376:     if err != nil {\n377:         return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to sign token: %w\", err)\n378:     }\n379:     \n380:     m.metrics.IssuedTotal.Inc()\n381:     return tokenString, nil\n382: }\n383: ```\n384: \n385: ### 5.3 中间件实现\n386: \n387: ```go\n388: // JWTMiddleware creates JWT authentication middleware\n389: func JWTMiddleware(manager *JWTManager, publicPaths []string) Middleware {\n390:     publicPathSet := make(map[string]bool)\n391:     for _, path := range publicPaths {\n392:         publicPathSet[path] = true\n393:     }\n394:     \n395:     return func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n396:         return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n397:             // Check if public path\n398:             if publicPathSet[r.URL.Path] {\n399:                 next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n400:                 return\n401:             }\n402:             \n403:             // Extract token\n404:             tokenString, err := extractToken(r, manager.config.AllowQueryParam)\n405:             if err != nil {\n406:                 http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusBadRequest)\n407:                 return\n408:             }\n409:             \n410:             // Validate token\n411:             claims, err := manager.ValidateToken(tokenString)\n412:             if err != nil {\n413:                 manager.metrics.ValidationErrorsTotal.WithLabelValues(getErrorType(err)).Inc()\n414:                 http.Error(w, \"Unauthorized\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n415:                 return\n416:             }\n417:             \n418:             // Add claims to context\n419:             ctx := context.WithValue(r.Context(), ContextKeyClaims, claims)\n420:             ctx = context.WithValue(ctx, ContextKeyUsername, claims.Subject)\n421:             \n422:             manager.metrics.ValidatedTotal.WithLabelValues(\"success\").Inc()\n423:             next.ServeHTTP(w, r.WithContext(ctx))\n424:         })\n425:     }\n426: }\n427: \n428: func extractToken(r *http.Request, allowQueryParam bool) (string, error) {\n429:     // Try Authorization header first\n430:     authHeader := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\")\n431:     if authHeader != \"\" {\n432:         parts := strings.SplitN(authHeader, \" \", 2)\n433:         if len(parts) == 2 && strings.ToLower(parts[0]) == \"bearer\" {\n434:             return parts[1], nil\n435:         }\n436:     }\n437:     \n438:     // Try query parameter if allowed\n439:     if allowQueryParam {\n440:         if token := r.URL.Query().Get(\"token\"); token != \"\" {\n441:             return token, nil\n442:         }\n443:     }\n444:     \n445:     return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"%w: no token found\", ErrMalformedToken)\n446: }\n447: ```\n448: \n449: ### 5.4 登录处理器\n450: \n451: ```go\n452: func (m *JWTManager) HandleLogin(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n453:     var creds UserCredentials\n454:     if err := json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode(&creds); err != nil {\n455:         writeError(w, \"bad request\", \"ERR_BAD_REQUEST\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n456:         return\n457:     }\n458:     \n459:     // Validate credentials\n460:     user, err := m.userValidator.Validate(creds.Username, creds.Password)\n461:     if err != nil {\n462:         writeError(w, \"invalid credentials\", \"ERR_INVALID_CREDENTIALS\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n463:         return\n464:     }\n465:     \n466:     // Issue tokens\n467:     accessToken, err := m.IssueToken(user)\n468:     if err != nil {\n469:         writeError(w, \"failed to issue token\", \"ERR_TOKEN_ISSUANCE_FAILED\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n470:         return\n471:     }\n472:     \n473:     refreshToken, err := m.IssueRefreshToken(user)\n474:     if err != nil {\n475:         writeError(w, \"failed to issue refresh token\", \"ERR_TOKEN_ISSUANCE_FAILED\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n476:         return\n477:     }\n478:     \n479:     response := LoginResponse{\n480:         AccessToken:  accessToken,\n481:         RefreshToken: refreshToken,\n482:         TokenType:    \"Bearer\",\n483:         ExpiresIn:    int64(m.config.Expiration.Seconds()),\n484:     }\n485:     \n486:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n487:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(response)\n488: }\n489: ```\n490: \n491: ### 5.5 密钥管理\n492: \n493: ```go\n494: // KeyManager handles JWT key loading and management\n495: type KeyManager struct {\n496:     config *JWTConfig\n497: }\n498: \n499: func (km *KeyManager) LoadKeys() error {\n500:     switch km.config.Algorithm {\n501:     case \"HS256\":\n502:         if km.config.Secret == \"\" {\n503:             return fmt.Errorf(\"JWT secret is required for HS256\")\n504:         }\n505:         km.config.Secret = os.Getenv(\"JWT_SECRET\") // Override from env if set\n506:     case \"RS256\":\n507:         if km.config.PrivateKeyPath == \"\" || km.config.PublicKeyPath == \"\" {\n508:             return fmt.Errorf(\"JWT key paths are required for RS256\")\n509:         }\n510:         \n511:         privateKeyData, err := os.ReadFile(km.config.PrivateKeyPath)\n512:         if err != nil {\n513:             return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to read private key: %w\", err)\n514:         }\n515:         \n516:         privateKey, err := jwt.ParseRSAPrivateKeyFromPEM(privateKeyData)\n517:         if err != nil {\n518:             return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse private key: %w\", err)\n519:         }\n520:         \n521:         publicKeyData, err := os.ReadFile(km.config.PublicKeyPath)\n522:         if err != nil {\n523:             return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to read public key: %w\", err)\n524:         }\n525:         \n526:         publicKey, err := jwt.ParseRSAPublicKeyFromPEM(publicKeyData)\n527:         if err != nil {\n528:             return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse public key: %w\", err)\n529:         }\n530:     }\n531:     \n532:     return nil\n533: }\n534: ```\n535: \n536: ---\n537: \n538: ## 6. 错误处理\n539: \n540: ### 6.1 错误类型\n541: \n542: ```go\n543: // JWT Errors\n544: var (\n545:     ErrMalformedToken     = errors.New(\"malformed token\")\n546:     ErrInvalidSignature   = errors.New(\"invalid signature\")\n547:     ErrTokenExpired       = errors.New(\"token expired\")\n548:     ErrInvalidAudience    = errors.New(\"invalid audience\")\n549:     ErrInvalidIssuer      = errors.New(\"invalid issuer\")\n550:     ErrUnauthorized       = errors.New(\"unauthorized\")\n551:     ErrInvalidCredentials = errors.New(\"invalid credentials\")\n552:     ErrInvalidRefreshToken = errors.New(\"invalid refresh token\")\n553: )\n554: \n555: // Error codes\n556: const (\n557:     ErrCodeMalformedToken      = \"ERR_MALFORMED_TOKEN\"\n558:     ErrCodeInvalidSignature   = \"ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE\"\n559:     ErrCodeTokenExpired        = \"ERR_TOKEN_EXPIRED\"\n560:     ErrCodeInvalidAudience    = \"ERR_INVALID_AUDIENCE\"\n561:     ErrCodeInvalidIssuer       = \"ERR_INVALID_ISSUER\"\n562:     ErrCodeUnauthorized       = \"ERR_UNAUTHORIZED\"\n563:     ErrCodeInvalidCredentials  = \"ERR_INVALID_CREDENTIALS\"\n564:     ErrCodeInvalidRefreshToken = \"ERR_INVALID_REFRESH_TOKEN\"\n565: )\n566: ```\n567: \n568: ### 6.2 错误处理策略\n569: \n570: | 错误场景 | HTTP 状态码 | 处理策略 |\n571: |----------|-------------|----------|\n572: | Token 格式错误 | 400 | 记录错误，返回 \"malformed token\" |\n573: | Token 签名无效 | 401 | 记录错误指标，返回 \"invalid signature\" |\n574: | Token 已过期 | 401 | 记录错误指标，返回 \"token expired\" |\n575: | Audience 不匹配 | 401 | 记录错误指标，返回 \"invalid audience\" |\n576: | Issuer 不匹配 | 401 | 记录错误指标，返回 \"invalid issuer\" |\n577: | 无效凭证 | 401 | 记录错误指标，返回 \"invalid credentials\" |\n578: | 无效刷新 Token | 401 | 记录错误指标，返回 \"invalid refresh token\" |\n579: \n580: ---\n581: \n582: ## 7. 监控指标\n583: \n584: ### 7.1 Prometheus 指标\n585: \n586: | Metric | Type | Labels | Description |\n587: |--------|------|--------|-------------|\n588: | `jwt_validated_total` | Counter | result (success/error) | JWT validation count |\n589: | `jwt_issued_total` | Counter | - | JWT token issuance count |\n590: | `jwt_refreshed_total` | Counter | result | JWT token refresh count |\n591: | `jwt_validation_errors_total` | Counter | error_type | JWT validation errors |\n592: \n593: ### 7.2 指标实现\n594: \n595: ```go\n596: type JWTMetrics struct {\n597:     ValidatedTotal        *prometheus.CounterVec\n598:     IssuedTotal          prometheus.Counter\n599:     RefreshedTotal       *prometheus.CounterVec\n600:     ValidationErrorsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec\n601: }\n602: \n603: func NewJWTMetrics() *JWTMetrics {\n604:     return &JWTMetrics{\n605:         ValidatedTotal: prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n606:             prometheus.CounterOpts{\n607:                 Name: \"jwt_validated_total\",\n608:                 Help: \"Total number of JWT validations\",\n609:             },\n610:             []string{\"result\"},\n611:         ),\n612:         IssuedTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(\n613:             prometheus.CounterOpts{\n614:                 Name: \"jwt_issued_total\",\n615:                 Help: \"Total number of JWT tokens issued\",\n616:             },\n617:         ),\n618:         RefreshedTotal: prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n619:             prometheus.CounterOpts{\n620:                 Name: \"jwt_refreshed_total\",\n621:                 Help: \"Total number of JWT token refreshes\",\n622:             },\n623:             []string{\"result\"},\n624:         ),\n625:         ValidationErrorsTotal: prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n626:             prometheus.CounterOpts{\n627:                 Name: \"jwt_validation_errors_total\",\n628:                 Help: \"Total number of JWT validation errors\",\n629:             },\n630:             []string{\"error_type\"},\n631:         ),\n632:     }\n633: }\n634: ```\n635: \n636: ---\n637: \n638: ## 8. 测试策略\n639: \n640: ### 8.1 单元测试\n641: \n642: | 模块 | 测试重点 |\n643: |------|----------|\n644: | `JWTManager` | Token 签发、验证、刷新、算法切换 |\n645: | `KeyManager` | 密钥加载、HS256/RS256 切换 |\n646: | `JWTMiddleware` | Token 提取、公开端点跳过、Context 传递 |\n647: | `LoginHandler` | 登录成功、失败、错误处理 |\n648: | `RefreshHandler` | 刷新成功、过期 Token 拒绝 |\n649: \n650: ### 8.2 测试场景\n651: \n652: | 场景 | 预期结果 |\n653: |------|----------|\n654: | 有效 JWT Token 验证 | 验证成功，Claims 正确解析 |\n655: | 过期 JWT Token 验证 | 返回 ErrTokenExpired |\n656: | 无效签名 JWT | 返回 ErrInvalidSignature |\n657: | 错误 Audience | 返回 ErrInvalidAudience |\n658: | 登录成功 | 返回 AccessToken 和 RefreshToken |\n659: | 登录失败（错误密码） | 返回 401 |\n660: | Token 刷新成功 | 返回新的 AccessToken |\n661: | Token 刷新（过期 RefreshToken） | 返回 401 |\n662: \n663: ### 8.3 测试覆盖率目标\n664: \n665: | 组件 | 目标覆盖率 |\n666: |------|-----------|\n667: | auth.go | 90% |\n668: | jwt.go (new) | 90% |\n669: \n670: ---\n671: \n672: ## 9. 实施计划\n673: \n674: ### Phase 1: 核心功能\n675: - [ ] 定义 JWTConfig 配置结构\n676: - [ ] 实现 JWTManager 核心逻辑\n677: - [ ] 实现 Token 签发和验证\n678: \n679: ### Phase 2: API 端点\n680: - [ ] 实现 /login 端点\n681: - [ ] 实现 /refresh 端点\n682: \n683: ### Phase 3: 中间件\n684: - [ ] 实现 JWT 中间件\n685: - [ ] 配置公开端点列表\n686: - [ ] 实现 Claims 传递到 Context\n687: \n688: ### Phase 4: 密钥管理\n689: - [ ] 实现 HS256 对称密钥支持\n690: - [ ] 实现 RS256 非对称密钥支持\n691: \n692: ### Phase 5: 监控和测试\n693: - [ ] 添加 Prometheus 指标\n694: - [ ] 编写单元测试\n695: - [ ] 集成测试\n696: \n697: ---\n698: \n699: ## 10. 依赖\n700: \n701: ### 10.1 外部依赖\n702: \n703: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n704: |---------|---------|---------|\n705: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | ^5.0.0 | JWT token handling |\n706: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | ^1.16.0 | Metrics |\n707: \n708: ### 10.2 内部依赖\n709: \n710: | Module | Purpose |\n711: |--------|---------|\n712: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Existing router module |\n713: \n714: ---\n715: \n716: ## 11. 参考\n717: \n718: - [Delta Spec: AR-011](changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md)\n719: - [Proposal](proposal.md)\n720: - [AR-010: Router Session Management](pkg/router/design.md)\n721: - [JWT RFC 7519](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519)\n722: - [golang-jwt library](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n\n(End of file - total 722 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-011\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Draft\n- **Base**: AR-010 (Session Management)\n\n## 1. 概述\n\n本设计文档聚焦于 **JWT 认证与签发** 功能，为 `pkg/router` 模块增加基于 JWT 的身份验证和令牌管理能力。该功能是 AR-010 会话管理的扩展，提供安全的 API 访问控制。\n\n### 1.1 目标\n\n- 实现 JWT Token 验证（支持 HS256、RS256 算法）\n- 实现 JWT Token 签发（登录接口）\n- 实现 Token 刷新接口\n- 支持可配置的 JWT 参数（Issuer、Audience、Expiry）\n- 提供 JWT 指标监控","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/design.md","time":{"start":1775849579918,"end":1775849579940}}}}
