{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775849591839,"sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","part":{"id":"prt_d78e2541d001AxJ3Vt61jTxSzT","messageID":"msg_d78e241e10018wymWpJZUw52Xm","sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849626484,"sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","part":{"id":"prt_d78e25904001vN3PFL4gX9rSYB","messageID":"msg_d78e241e10018wymWpJZUw52Xm","sessionID":"ses_2871e069fffeDDE9bhBiHTD0uC","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_92fca8b7e5da43bbb64c842a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: JWT Configuration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Add JWT config fields to `Config` struct — `JWTEnabled`, `JWTAlgorithm`, `JWTSecret`, `JWTPrivateKeyPath`, `JWTPublicKeyPath`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTAudience`, `JWTExpiration`, `JWTRefreshExpiration`, `JWTClockSkew`, `JWTAllowQueryParam`\n- [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` JWT defaults — algorithm \"HS256\", issuer \"agentcube\", expiry \"1h\", refresh expiry \"24h\", clock skew \"30s\"\n- [ ] **1.3** Add JWT dependency to `go.mod` — `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: JWT Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTConfig` struct with all JWT settings\n- [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `Claims` struct embedding `jwt.RegisteredClaims` with custom fields (Roles, TenantID, Namespace)\n- [ ] **2.3** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserCredentials` struct for login request\n- [ ] **2.4** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `LoginResponse` struct for login response\n- [ ] **2.5** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `TokenRefreshRequest` struct\n- [ ] **2.6** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserValidator` interface\n- [ ] **2.7** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserClaims` struct\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: JWT Errors\n\n- [ ] **3.1** Define JWT error variables — `ErrMalformedToken`, `ErrInvalidSignature`, `ErrTokenExpired`, `ErrInvalidAudience`, `ErrInvalidIssuer`, `ErrUnauthorized`, `ErrInvalidCredentials`, `ErrInvalidRefreshToken`\n- [ ] **3.2** Define JWT error code constants\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: JWT Manager - Core\n\n- [ ] **4.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTManager` struct with config, keys, metrics, userValidator\n- [ ] **4.2** Implement `NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig, validator UserValidator)` — initialize manager and load keys\n- [ ] **4.3** Implement key loading for HS256 (symmetric key from config/env)\n- [ ] **4.4** Implement key loading for RS256 (load private/public keys from files)\n- [ ] **4.5** Write unit test: HS256 key loading from config\n- [ ] **4.6** Write unit test: RS256 key loading from files\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: JWT Token Validation\n\n- [ ] **5.1** Implement `JWTManager.ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*Claims, error)` — parse and validate JWT\n- [ ] **5.2** Implement HS256 token validation with secret key\n- [ ] **5.3** Implement RS256 token validation with public key\n- [ ] **5.4** Handle signature validation errors\n- [ ] **5.5** Handle expiration validation with clock skew\n- [ ] **5.6** Handle issuer validation\n- [ ] **5.7** Handle audience validation\n- [ ] **5.8** Write unit test: Validate valid HS256 token\n- [ ] **5.9** Write unit test: Validate expired token returns error\n- [ ] **5.10** Write unit test: Validate invalid signature returns error\n- [ ] **5.11** Write unit test: Validate malformed token returns error\n- [ ] **5.12** Write unit test: Validate wrong audience returns error\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: JWT Token Issuance\n\n- [ ] **6.1** Implement `JWTManager.IssueToken(user *UserClaims) (string, error)` — issue access token\n- [ ] **6.2** Implement `JWTManager.IssueRefreshToken(user *UserClaims) (string, error)` — issue refresh token\n- [ ] **6.3** Implement HS256 token signing\n- [ ] **6.4** Implement RS256 token signing\n- [ ] **6.5** Set claims: sub, exp, iat, nbf, iss, roles, tenant_id, namespace\n- [ ] **6.6** Write unit test: Issue token with correct claims\n- [ ] **6.7** Write unit test: Issue token with configured expiry\n- [ ] **6.8** Write unit test: Issue token with configured issuer\n- [ ] **6.9** Write unit test: RS256 token issuance\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: JWT Middleware\n\n- [ ] **7.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go` — `JWTMiddleware` function\n- [ ] **7.2** Implement token extraction from Authorization header (Bearer token)\n- [ ] **7.3** Implement token extraction from query parameter (when AllowQueryParam is true)\n- [ ] **7.4** Implement public path check — skip JWT validation for public endpoints\n- [ ] **7.5** Integrate JWT validation into middleware chain\n- [ ] **7.6** Store claims in request context\n- [ ] **7.7** Store username in request context\n- [ ] **7.8** Write unit test: Extract token from Authorization header\n- [ ] **7.9** Write unit test: Extract token from query parameter\n- [ ] **7.10** Write unit test: Public endpoint bypasses JWT validation\n- [ ] **7.11** Write unit test: Protected endpoint rejects missing token\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Login Handler\n\n- [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_handler.go` — `HandleLogin` function\n- [ ] **8.2** Decode and validate UserCredentials from request body\n- [ ] **8.3** Call userValidator.Validate() with username/password\n- [ ] **8.4** Issue access token and refresh token on success\n- [ ] **8.5** Return LoginResponse with token, type, expires_in\n- [ ] **8.6** Return 401 on invalid credentials\n- [ ] **8.7** Register `/login` endpoint in router\n- [ ] **8.8** Write unit test: Login with valid credentials returns token\n- [ ] **8.9** Write unit test: Login with invalid credentials returns 401\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: Refresh Handler\n\n- [ ] **9.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_handler.go` — `HandleRefresh` function\n- [ ] **9.2** Decode TokenRefreshRequest from request body\n- [ ] **9.3** Validate refresh token\n- [ ] **9.4** Issue new access token\n- [ ] **9.5** Return new access token with expires_in\n- [ ] **9.6** Return 401 on invalid/expired refresh token\n- [ ] **9.7** Register `/refresh` endpoint in router\n- [ ] **9.8** Write unit test: Refresh with valid token returns new access token\n- [ ] **9.9** Write unit test: Refresh with expired token returns 401\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: Router Integration\n\n- [ ] **10.1** Update router initialization to create JWTManager when JWTEnabled\n- [ ] **10.2** Add JWT middleware to handler chain\n- [ ] **10.3** Configure public paths list: `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/metrics`, `/login`, `/refresh`\n- [ ] **10.4** Add login and refresh endpoints to router\n- [ ] **10.5** Write unit test: Router with JWT enabled applies middleware\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11: JWT Metrics\n\n- [ ] **11.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_metrics.go` — `JWTMetrics` struct\n- [ ] **11.2** Implement `jwt_validated_total` counter with result label\n- [ ] **11.3** Implement `jwt_issued_total` counter\n- [ ] **11.4** Implement `jwt_refreshed_total` counter with result label\n- [ ] **11.5** Implement `jwt_validation_errors_total` counter with error_type label\n- [ ] **11.6** Integrate metrics into JWTManager\n- [ ] **11.7** Increment metrics on validation success/failure\n- [ ] **11.8** Increment metrics on token issuance\n- [ ] **11.9** Increment metrics on token refresh\n\n---\n\n## Phase 12: Validation\n\n- [ ] **12.1** `go build ./pkg/router/...` — successful compilation\n- [ ] **12.2** `go test ./pkg/router/... -v` — all unit tests pass\n- [ ] **12.3** Test: JWT with default config uses HS256, 1h expiry\n- [ ] **12.4** Test: JWT with custom config uses RS256, 24h expiry\n- [ ] **12.5** Test: Valid JWT token validates successfully\n- [ ] **12.6** Test: Expired JWT token returns 401\n- [ ] **12.7** Test: Invalid signature returns 401\n- [ ] **12.8** Test: Malformed token returns 400\n- [ ] **12.9** Test: Claims extracted and available in context\n- [ ] **12.10** Test: Login endpoint issues JWT token\n- [ ] **12.11** Test: Token refresh endpoint works\n- [ ] **12.12** Test: Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n- [ ] **12.13** Test: JWT metrics are exported\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` — JWT token handling\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` — Metrics\n- AR-010 (completed) — Router Session Management\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n- Design: `pkg/router/design.md`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go\">\nERROR [15:2] \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch\" imported and not used\nERROR [66:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [81:9] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [95:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [109:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [132:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [160:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/api